 contribution to current debates about terrorism. It also analyzes the public debate in Germany about the historical, moral, and political significance of the deliberate killing of up to 600,000 German civilians by the British and American air forces. This pioneering collaboration provides a platform for a wide range of views—some of which are controversial—on a highly topical, painful, and morally challenging subject.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBombing, AerialxHistoryx20th centuryxGermany. 0aBombing, AerialzGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aBombing, Aerial. 0aEthics. 0aMilitary campaigns. 0aMilitary operations, Aerial. 0aTerrorismxHistoryx20th century. 0aTerrorism. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAerial operations. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xCampaignsxGermany. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMoral and ethical aspects. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh1 aBeck, Earl R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConnelly, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarrett, Stephen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKettenacker, Lothar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKopf, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLackey, Douglas P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarkusen, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiddlebrook, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrimoratz, Igor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrimoratz, Igor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aimora, Igor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook 